than when you were supposed to be here.


944
00:51:12.731 --> 00:51:13.537
Now, what happened?

945
00:51:14.364 --> 00:51:14.917
It's a long story.

946
00:51:14.986 --> 00:51:17.175
You know, you and Julia need to talk.

947
00:51:17.236 --> 00:51:20.647
I can take Jeremiah shopping.
I'm an excellent gift consultant.


948
00:51:20.852 --> 00:51:23.380
Yes, Dudley. I want Dudley.

949
00:51:23.441 --> 00:51:25.147
Wait a minute.
I wanted to take him shopping.


950
00:51:25.776 --> 00:51:27.646
You two have more important
things to talk about.


951
00:51:27.707 --> 00:51:30.454
-Dud-ley! Dud-ley! Dud-ley!
-Jeremiah.


952
00:51:30.515 --> 00:51:33.780
We'll be right across the street
at the toy store. Okay?


953
00:51:33.841 --> 00:51:35.328
-Julia! Julia!
-Dud-ley!


954
00:51:35.389 --> 00:51:38.391
-Jere-miah! Put your hat on.
-Dud-ley! Dud-ley!


955
00:51:40.260 --> 00:51:41.967
-So, who are we shopping for?
-Grandma.


956
00:51:42.046 --> 00:51:44.205
-Any idea what she wants?
-A new ashtray.


957
00:51:44.266 --> 00:51:47.633
-Mom took all her old ones.
-Let's get something for Hakim.


958
00:51:48.198 --> 00:51:49.102
So, what happened?

959
00:51:54.205 --> 00:51:54.906
Julia.

960
00:52:00.211 --> 00:52:00.816
I...

961
00:52:03.199 --> 00:52:05.241
I've decided to accept
Joe Hamilton's offer.


962
00:52:08.572 --> 00:52:10.345
Julia, did you hear me?

963
00:52:12.540 --> 00:52:14.783
I heard you. I just can't
believe what I've heard.


964
00:52:14.844 --> 00:52:15.810
-Then let me explain.

965
00:52:16.097 --> 00:52:17.751
Excuse me. Can I get you anything?

966
00:52:17.851 --> 00:52:20.049
Oh, no, no, no. 
No, thank you.

967
00:52:20.133 --> 00:52:20.998
Okay.

968
00:52:23.007 --> 00:52:27.393
Listen, Saul was there,
Mary Halford, Andy and Osbert.


969
00:52:27.880 --> 00:52:28.930
But what were they doing there?

970
00:52:28.991 --> 00:52:32.932
Every one of them was begging me,
arguing with me, blackmailing me.


971
00:52:32.993 --> 00:52:35.712
Blackmail!
They're gonna put in a new boiler tomorrow.


972
00:52:35.780 --> 00:52:38.150
-Henry, he bought you for a boiler?
-Shh. Julia.


973
00:52:40.890 --> 00:52:43.874
Sorry. Sorry. Excuse us. 
Of course not!

974
00:52:44.254 --> 00:52:46.405
-Oooooh...
-Julia, let me show you something.


975
00:52:46.957 --> 00:52:48.336
Julia, Julia...

976
00:52:49.821 --> 00:52:52.536
he is building the most beautiful church
you've ever seen.


977
00:52:52.597 --> 00:52:54.892
Look at that.
Day care centre, youth centre.


978
00:52:54.953 --> 00:52:56.852
Henry, he is building
a shrine to himself!


979
00:52:57.114 --> 00:52:58.303
Eight years, Julia.

980
00:53:00.183 --> 00:53:01.316
And what do I
have to show for it?

981
00:53:01.829 --> 00:53:05.609
So you give up our lives
without even talking to me, Henry?


982
00:53:05.670 --> 00:53:09.499
This solves all of our problems, Julia.
Why can't you see that?


983
00:53:09.560 --> 00:53:12.713
My father trusted you with St. Matt's.
How dare you walk out on it like this!


984
00:53:12.782 --> 00:53:15.307
All right, all right.
