1468
01:19:19.112 --> 01:19:22.220
And I'm gonna say it again.
Oh, my Lord.


1469
01:19:23.016 --> 01:19:24.778
Ma, he's been very kind. That's all.

1470
01:19:25.652 --> 01:19:27.723
At least he's got time for me.

1471
01:19:28.995 --> 01:19:31.714
Julia,
Henry can't be ten places at once.


1472
01:19:33.086 --> 01:19:35.172
And don't tell me
that your daddy could.


1473
01:19:36.643 --> 01:19:38.620
Now pull yourself together, young lady.

1474
01:19:39.939 --> 01:19:41.391
You're a married woman.

1475
01:19:42.748 --> 01:19:43.599
Oh, Ma,

1476
01:19:44.512 --> 01:19:46.212
I can look in the window.

1477
01:19:47.299 --> 01:19:48.745
Even if I don't buy.

1478
01:19:49.909 --> 01:19:54.159
Well, you just better not go window
shopping with money in your pocket.


1479
01:19:55.805 --> 01:19:59.444
And you better not be puttin' anything
in the layaway plan, either.


1480
01:19:59.612 --> 01:20:00.627
You hear me?

1481
01:20:01.234 --> 01:20:02.226
Oh, Ma.

1482
01:20:11.918 --> 01:20:13.399
♪ Two turtledoves ♪

1483
01:20:13.620 --> 01:20:16.538
♪ And a partridge
in a pear tree ♪

1484
01:20:18.383 --> 01:20:21.546
-Let's do it again.
-Oh, no more, Jer, please.


1485
01:20:21.607 --> 01:20:22.943
-Oooh!
-Your dad's home.


1486
01:20:24.070 --> 01:20:26.971
Daddy, where were you?

1487
01:20:27.032 --> 01:20:29.078
I'm sorry, Jer. I really am.

1488
01:20:30.007 --> 01:20:32.980
I just can't understand why the traffic
was so bad. We'll go tomorrow, okay?


1489
01:20:33.112 --> 01:20:36.505
Okay. I did skating, Dad.

1490
01:20:36.566 --> 01:20:38.695
You did? Good for you.

1491
01:20:38.818 --> 01:20:43.084
And I got Billy Eldridge
home for Christmas.


1492
01:20:43.589 --> 01:20:45.832
They dropped the charges, Henry.
How'd you do it?


1493
01:20:46.018 --> 01:20:50.614
I just remembered you gotta look someone
in the eye to see if they're innocent.


1494
01:20:52.273 --> 01:20:53.459
So it wasn't that hard.

1495
01:20:55.206 --> 01:20:56.979
-Daddy?
-Yes, son?


1496
01:20:57.342 --> 01:21:00.007
-Skating isn't hard, neither.
-It isn't?


1497
01:21:00.068 --> 01:21:00.721
No.

1498
01:21:01.692 --> 01:21:02.746
Your mom taught you, huh?

1499
01:21:02.994 --> 01:21:05.861
Dudley and Mom. It was fun!

1500
01:21:10.067 --> 01:21:11.309
Dudley went skating with you?

1501
01:21:11.696 --> 01:21:13.694
We waited for you, Henry.
You didn't miss much at all.


1502
01:21:23.794 --> 01:21:26.205
Ah, Henry! Just the
man I wanted to see.


1503
01:21:26.400 --> 01:21:28.136
I've been working on this Christmas Eve...

1504
01:21:28.197 --> 01:21:29.774
Keep away from my wife.

1505
01:21:31.538 --> 01:21:32.518
What'd I do now?

1506
01:21:33.502 --> 01:21:34.605
You take her to lunch.

1507
01:21:34.936 --> 01:21:36.159
Well, you were late, Henry.

1508
01:21:36.227 --> 01:21:37.870
-You take her to Jazzie's.
-You asked me to.


1509
01:21:37.931 --> 01:21:40.893
You take her skating.
What kind of man do you think I am?


1510
01:21:41.766 --> 01:21:43.216
Keep the hell away from her.

1511
01:21:44.362 --> 01:21:45.969
Henry, you're a man of God.

1512
01:21:47.138 --> 01:21:48.392
That doesn't mean I'm blind.

1513
01:21:49.259 --> 01:21:51.127
Now, I've seen the way
she looks at you.


1514
01:21:51.482 --> 01:21:53.749
Really? I mean, really.

1515
01:21:54.166 --> 01:21:55.231
All right, fine.

1516
01:21:57.177 --> 01:21:58.318
I want you to leave now.

1517
01:21:58.562 --> 01:21:59.784
-Now?
-Yes, now.


1518
01:22:00.696 --> 01:22:03.601
I don't think I can do that.
Check the angel handbook.


1519
01:22:03.662 --> 01:22:04.548
It says I...

1520
01:22:05.262 --> 01:22:07.264
can't leave until I'm through, I think.

1521
01:22:07.325 --> 01:22:09.492
You see, it says right here...

1522
01:22:09.587 --> 01:22:11.202
Wait a minute. Hey! Henry!

1523
01:22:14.716 --> 01:22:15.448
What was that?

1524
01:22:17.158 --> 01:22:18.403
-Oooh!
-My goodness!


1525
01:22:21.611 --> 01:22:22.213
What?

1526
01:22:22.572 --> 01:22:24.468
-You're in trouble.
-What was that?


1527
01:22:26.054 --> 01:22:26.628
What is that?

1528
01:22:26.689 --> 01:22:28.818
It wasn't a sign that there's a new pope.
I'll tell you that.


1529
01:22:28.879 --> 01:22:30.012
What do you mean?

1530
01:22:30.073 --> 01:22:31.933
-You're in trouble. You
want me out of the house.


1531
01:22:31.994 --> 01:22:35.157
-Yes, I want you out.
-I'm not the problem. It wasn't me.


1532
01:22:35.319 --> 01:22:37.981
It wasn't me!
-Who are you talking to? Get out of my house!


1533
01:22:38.134 --> 01:22:39.631
What is going on in here?

1534
01:22:40.077 --> 01:22:42.382
I am terminating Dudley's services.
I want him out of here.


1535
01:22:42.443 --> 01:22:43.424
Is that what you want, Julia?

1536
01:22:43.485 --> 01:22:45.079
It isn't a question of what she wants.

1537
01:22:47.250 --> 01:22:50.349
All right, Julia, you're a part of this.
You say.


1538
01:22:52.049 --> 01:22:53.669
You two stop this right now.
Just stop it!


1539
01:22:55.238 --> 01:22:56.623
You hear me?

1540
01:23:00.163 --> 01:23:02.495
-You see what you did?
-It's not about me.


1541
01:23:02.556 --> 01:23:05.467
You and Julia would have these problems
even if I never showed up.


1542
01:23:05.875 --> 01:23:07.353
You've forgotten what's important,

1543
01:23:07.809 --> 01:23:08.913
for you and for her.

1544
01:23:10.594 --> 01:23:12.453
And you're going to remind me, I'm sure.

1545
01:23:12.556 --> 01:23:14.659
St. Matt's is more
than just a church, Henry.


1546
01:23:15.125 --> 01:23:17.378
It's the glue that holds everything
together in this neighbourhood.


1547
01:23:17.439 --> 01:23:18.505
And you mark my word,

1548
01:23:19.074 --> 01:23:22.566
without it, this neighbourhood
will fall, I guarantee it.


1549
01:23:23.078 --> 01:23:25.090
And Julia will never
look at you the same.


1550
01:23:36.685 --> 01:23:37.534
Hey, handsome.

1551
01:23:38.777 --> 01:23:40.149
Come and walk me across the street.

1552
01:23:40.210 --> 01:23:41.994
I gotta take this plate
over to Bessie Adams.


1553
01:23:42.685 --> 01:23:45.054
-Well, actually, I was...
-Walk me!


1554
01:23:46.502 --> 01:23:47.291
Delighted.

1555
01:23:53.142 --> 01:23:56.207
-I heard what you two were talking about.
-Really?


1556
01:23:56.966 --> 01:24:00.580
Now, you know I don't usually
pry into other folks' business.


1557
01:24:00.823 --> 01:24:01.339
Uh-huh.

1558
01:24:02.255 --> 01:24:03.088
Hold on a second.

1559
01:24:05.942 --> 01:24:07.369
Mmm-mm!

1560
01:24:09.813 --> 01:24:10.607
Now,

1561
01:24:11.380 --> 01:24:14.439
what are you doing to my daughter?

1562
01:24:14.500 --> 01:24:17.432
Mrs. Coleman, it's all right,
I promise you.


1563
01:24:17.846 --> 01:24:19.433
Nothin' is all right, Dudley,

1564
01:24:19.600 --> 01:24:23.280
when I see a married woman
look at a man that way.


1565
01:24:24.128 --> 01:24:26.436
I'm just tryin' to help them,
that's all.


1566
01:24:29.137 --> 01:24:32.072
You really shouldn't smoke.
Our time here on Earth is precious.


1567
01:24:32.527 --> 01:24:33.454
That's right.

1568
01:24:33.996 --> 01:24:37.821
And you know the most precious time
of all is time spent with your family.


1569
01:24:39.440 --> 01:24:41.794
Now, you know I'm supposed
to only be here through Christmas.


1570
01:24:43.171 --> 01:24:45.884
But I will conveniently
have a hip injury...


1571
01:24:46.528 --> 01:24:48.889
and stay to the year
2000 if I have to.

1572
01:24:49.357 --> 01:24:50.766
Do you understand
what I'm sayin' to you?


1573
01:24:50.827 --> 01:24:52.290
-I do now.
-Mm-hmm.


1574
01:24:52.833 --> 01:24:56.796
Look, I'm havin' a little trouble
tryin' to get through to Henry.


1575
01:24:56.857 --> 01:24:59.842
Now, Julia, on the other hand,
she's wonderful. She deserves...


1576
01:24:59.903 --> 01:25:02.997
What are you talkin' about what Julia
deserves and what she don't?


1577
01:25:03.657 --> 01:25:05.270
She's Henry's wife.

1578
01:25:06.801 --> 01:25:07.839
Don't worry. I...

1579
01:25:09.506 --> 01:25:11.587
I'm sure she'll forget me
as soon as I leave.


1580
01:25:12.594 --> 01:25:14.893
She'll forget herself
if you go on like this.


1581
01:25:15.916 --> 01:25:17.822
Marguerite, is that you?

1582
01:25:17.933 --> 01:25:19.239
I'm comin', Bessie!

1583
01:25:20.061 --> 01:25:21.119
Now, Dudley,

1584
01:25:21.886 --> 01:25:23.715
you are a charming person.

1585
01:25:25.521 --> 01:25:27.181
You go charm somebody else.

1586
01:25:27.789 --> 01:25:28.469
Okay?

1587
01:25:41.149 --> 01:25:42.827
Bessie, I'm comin' in.

1588
01:25:44.759 --> 01:25:46.903
Did I tell you I quit smokin'?

1589
01:25:47.282 --> 01:25:49.681
I'm so proud of you, sugar.

1590
01:25:56.149 --> 01:25:57.311
Watch it. Don't slip now.

1591
01:25:57.372 --> 01:25:58.773
Come on, babies, let's go.

1592
01:25:59.344 --> 01:26:01.722
Thank you so much. Now you
have a lot more room.


1593
01:26:02.608 --> 01:26:04.824
-Bye.
-Hi, Dudley!


1594
01:26:05.037 --> 01:26:07.179
I'm just baby-sitting Jeremiah.

1595
01:26:07.278 --> 01:26:11.210
-Mommy, Mommy! Here, puppy.
-Get away from that dog!


1596
01:26:11.271 --> 01:26:13.432
-Go ahead!
-Jeremiah! Jeremiah!


1597
01:26:13.668 --> 01:26:14.503
Saul!

1598
01:26:16.845 --> 01:26:17.772
Where's he goin'now?

1599
01:26:19.580 --> 01:26:21.147
Thank you so much for the ride.

1600
01:26:21.281 --> 01:26:22.898
I know you had to
go out of your way.

1601
01:26:23.590 --> 01:26:25.034
The first five minutes
of The Nutcracker


1602
01:26:25.095 --> 01:26:26.443
hasn't changed any since last year.

1603
01:26:27.681 --> 01:26:29.898
I'll make 'em leave before the
bows so we can come and get you.


1604
01:26:29.959 --> 01:26:31.144
-Oh, thank you.

1605
01:26:33.323 --> 01:26:34.157
-Um...
-Um...


1606
01:26:36.927 --> 01:26:37.651
Thanks.

1607
01:26:37.737 --> 01:26:38.582
Okay.

1608
01:26:41.288 --> 01:26:43.551
-Bye-bye.
-Bye!


1609
01:26:43.724 --> 01:26:46.128
No time for that, Saul.
Come on, we're gonna be late.


1610
01:26:46.189 --> 01:26:49.220
Oh, Santa, just leave
that man under my tree...


1611
01:26:49.840 --> 01:26:50.914
if he'll fit.

